title: Bachelorette Angie Kent's slender frame ahead of premiere
text:
There has been a lot of hype surrounding Angie Kent's season of The Bachelorette.

And the former Gogglebox star started making headlines while doing the media rounds on Wednesday morning, just hours ahead of the show's premiere.

The 29-year-old was spotted outside the KIIS FM studios in North Ryde, following an interview with The Kyle and Jackie 'O' show.

Stunning: Australia's incoming Bachelorette Angie Kent flaunted her svelte figure outside KIIS studios in North Ryde on Wednesday after an interview with The Kyle and Jackie O show

She flaunted her slender frame in a pretty matching patterned top and shorts, accessorised with perspex stilettos and hoop earrings.

The beauty kept her makeup simple and pulled her long blonde tresses back.

During her interview with Kyle Sandilands, Angie addressed the feud she has with Married At First Sight's Jessika Power.

Gorgeous: She flaunted her slender frame in a pretty matching patterned top and shorts

Busy gal: The 29-year-old is doing the media rounds ahead of her Bachelorette premiere on Wednesday night

When the shock jock brought up Power, Angie channelled Mariah Carey by responding: 'I don't know her!'

The rivalry between the two women began on Sunday, after Angie was quoted in a newspaper as saying that MAFS was 'super trash'.

She went on to add: 'I don't know Jess. I didn't even watch her season of MAFS because I was in the jungle [on... Get Me Out Of Here!]

'I don't know her': During her interview, Angie addressed rumours she's in a feud with Married At First Sight's Jessika Power, telling Kyle Sandilands she 'doesn't know where it that [feud] came from'

'I don't know her. I don't know where that [the feud] has come from.'

Elsewhere Ten made a major slip-up this week, revealing one of Angie's suitors, Ryan Anderson, was an intruder of the show.

And tellingly, Ryan appears to be the only contestant Angie is following on Instagram.
description: There has been a lot of hype surrounding Angie Kent's season of The Bachelorette.
authors: David Wu For Daily Mail Australia
